<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Why is this board so concerned about enlightening/supporting "Nesticle" (or any old emulator's) users? If iNES were to be unofficially revamped and Nesticle "broke", wouldn't that be all the more reason for them to move up? If they bitch, why should anyone here care?</div>They wouldn't break: older emulators (are supposed to) ignore the reserved bits.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Instead of extending the reserved bits, I think it'd be better for authors to agree upon new mapper numbers. Perhaps duplicates and useless mappers could be the first to be replaced.</div>That would create incompatibilities between iNES header revisions. Besides, 256 possibilities can be too little.</div>

